<h2><strong>NY Sports Betting Apps FAQ</strong></h2>
<h3>Are Mobile Sports Betting Apps Legal In New York?</h3>
<p><strong>Yes</strong>: Sports betting apps are now legal and active in New York, as of Saturday, Jan. 8, 2022, at 9 a.m. ET when the state officially launched online sports betting. FanDuel Sportsbook, DraftKings Sportsbook, Caesars Sportsbook and BetRivers were the first four to market, while BetMGM and PointsBet ultimately followed suit. </p>
<h3>Which Is The Best Sports Betting App In New York?</h3>
<p><strong>DraftKings Sportsbook</strong>: AMNY, along with many others, touts DraftKings Sportsbook as the best sports betting app on the market today. Obviously, sports gamblers can&#8217;t go wrong with other options such as Caesars Sportsbook.</p>
<h3>Which Sports Can I Bet On In New York?</h3>
<p><strong>Many (save for in-state collegiate athletics)</strong>: Just like New Jersey, New York does not allow in-state collegiate betting. This means that any collegiate athletics representing a school from the state of New York cannot be wagered on.</p>
<p>A prohibited sports event means any collegiate sport or athletic event that takes place in New York or a sport or athletic event where any New York college team participates regardless of where the event takes place.</p>
<h3>Is Online Sports Betting Legal In New York?</h3>
<p><strong>Yes</strong>: The online piece of NY sports betting officially went live on Jan. 8, 2022, at 9 a.m. ET.</p>
<h3>When Did Sports Betting Go Live in New York?</h3>
<p><strong>2019</strong>: Retail sports betting in New York went live in 2019. Jan. 8, 2022, at 9 a.m. ET is when NY online sports betting officially launched.</p>
<h3>Will I Have to be in New York to Bet?</h3>
<p><strong>Yes</strong>: You can bet on sports in any of the approved retail sports betting locations in New York.</p>
<h3>Do I Have to be a New York Resident to Bet?</h3>
<p><strong>No</strong>: It is not required that the sports gambler resides in New York to place wagers in person.</p>
<h3>What Types of Bets Can I Place in New York?</h3>
<p><strong>A wide variety</strong>: New York offers many of the same types of bets seen in the online space. Straight bets (Moneyline, spread, O/U), Parlays &amp; Accumulators, Pleasers &amp; Teasers, Player &amp; Championship, Futures Live Betting Props &amp; Exotics</p>
<h3>What is the New York Sports Betting Tax Rate?</h3>
<p><strong>51%</strong>: New York&#8217;s sports betting tax rate on revenue is currently 51%, which is tied for first in the country (New Hampshire).</p>
<h3>How Old Must I Be to Place a Bet in New York?</h3>
<p><strong>21 years of age or older</strong>: As is the case in all states where sports betting is legal, gamblers must be at least 21 years of age.</p>
<h3>How Many Mobile Sportsbooks Are Available to Use in New York?</h3>
<p><strong>8</strong>: FanDuel, DraftKings, Caesars, BetMGM, PointsBet, BetRivers, WynnBET and Resorts World are all legal and live.</p>
